A '''bidirectional current''' is one which both charges and discharges at once.

==Usage==
Complicated systems which have integrated [[recharge (battery)|recharging]] capability sometimes resort to using bidirectional currents, as in [[laptop computer|Laptop]]s or other systems. Monitoring of a bidirectional current is required for a laptop to report the [[rechargeable battery|battery]] level and charging status.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maximintegrated.com/app-notes/index.mvp/id/1949|title = MaxIntegrated-Bidirectional Currents}}</ref> Components are available for this purpose.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.analog.com/media/en/technical-documentation/data-sheets/AD8218.pdf|title=www.analog.com/media/en/technical-documentation/data-sheets/AD8218.pdf}}</ref>

